aVWhite House photo by Eric Draper No one can deny the success of freedom, but some men rage and fight against it.
p38
aVAnd one of the main sources of reaction and opposition is radical Islam -- the perversion by a few of a noble faith into an ideology of terror and death.
p39
aVTerrorists like bin Laden are serious about mass murder -- and all of us must take their declared intentions seriously.
p40
aVThey seek to impose a heartless system of totalitarian control throughout the Middle East, and arm themselves with weapons of mass murder.
p41
aVTheir aim is to seize power in Iraq, and use it as a safe haven to launch attacks against America and the world.
p42
aVLacking the military strength to challenge us directly, the terrorists have chosen the weapon of fear.
p43
aVWhen they murder children at a school in Beslan, or blow up commuters in London, or behead a bound captive, the terrorists hope these horrors will break our will, allowing the violent to inherit the Earth.
p44
aVBut they have miscalculated: We love our freedom, and we will fight to keep it.
p45
aV(Applause.)
p46
aVIn a time of testing, we cannot find security by abandoning our commitments and retreating within our borders.
p47
aVIf we were to leave these vicious attackers alone, they would not leave us alone.
p48
aVThey would simply move the battlefield to our own shores.
p49
aVThere is no peace in retreat.
p50
aVAnd there is no honor in retreat.
p51
aVBy allowing radical Islam to work its will -- by leaving an assaulted world to fend for itself -- we would signal to all that we no longer believe in our own ideals, or even in our own courage.
p52
aVBut our enemies and our friends can be certain: The United States will not retreat from the world, and we will never surrender to evil.
p53
aV(Applause.)
p54
aVAmerica rejects the false comfort of isolationism.
p55
aVWe are the nation that saved liberty in Europe, and liberated death camps, and helped raise up democracies, and faced down an evil empire.
p56
aVOnce again, we accept the call of history to deliver the oppressed and move this world toward peace.
p57
aVWe remain on the offensive against terror networks.
p58
aVWe have killed or captured many of their leaders -- and for the others, their day will come.
