aVWhite House photo by Eric Draper We remain on the offensive in Afghanistan, where a fine President and a National Assembly are fighting terror while building the institutions of a new democracy.
p62
aVWe're on the offensive in Iraq, with a clear plan for victory.
p63
aVFirst, we're helping Iraqis build an inclusive government, so that old resentments will be eased and the insurgency will be marginalized.
p64
aVSecond, we're continuing reconstruction efforts, and helping the Iraqi government to fight corruption and build a modern economy, so all Iraqis can experience the benefits of freedom.
p65
aVAnd, third, we're striking terrorist targets while we train Iraqi forces that are increasingly capable of defeating the enemy.
p66
aVIraqis are showing their courage every day, and we are proud to be their allies in the cause of freedom.
p67
aV(Applause.)
p68
aVOur work in Iraq is difficult because our enemy is brutal.
p69
aVBut that brutality has not stopped the dramatic progress of a new democracy.
p70
aVIn less than three years, the nation has gone from dictatorship to liberation, to sovereignty, to a constitution, to national elections.
p71
aVAt the same time, our coalition has been relentless in shutting off terrorist infiltration, clearing out insurgent strongholds, and turning over territory to Iraqi security forces.
p72
aVI am confident in our plan for victory; I am confident in the will of the Iraqi people; I am confident in the skill and spirit of our military.
p73
aVFellow citizens, we are in this fight to win, and we are winning.
p74
aV(Applause.)
p75
aVThe road of victory is the road that will take our troops home.
p76
aVAs we make progress on the ground, and Iraqi forces increasingly take the lead, we should be able to further decrease our troop levels -- but those decisions will be made by our military commanders, not by politicians in Washington, D.C.
p77
aV(Applause.)
p78
aVOur coalition has learned from our experience in Iraq.
p79
aVWe've adjusted our military tactics and changed our approach to reconstruction.
p80
aVAlong the way, we have benefitted from responsible criticism and counsel offered by members of Congress of both parties.
p81
aVIn the coming year, I will continue to reach out and seek your good advice.
p82
aVYet, there is a difference between responsible criticism that aims for success, and defeatism that refuses to acknowledge anything but failure.
p83
aV(Applause.)
p84
aVHindsight alone is not wisdom, and second-guessing is not a strategy.
p85
aV(Applause.)
p86
aVWith so much in the balance, those of us in public office have a duty to speak with candor.
p87
aVA sudden withdrawal of our forces from Iraq would abandon our Iraqi allies to death and prison, would put men like bin Laden and Zarqawi in charge of a strategic country, and show that a pledge from America means little.
p88
aVMembers of Congress, however we feel about the decisions and debates of the past, our nation has only one option: We must keep our word, defeat our enemies, and stand behind the American military in this vital mission.
p89
aV(Applause.)
