aVOur offensive against terror involves more than military action.
p109
aVUltimately, the only way to defeat the terrorists is to defeat their dark vision of hatred and fear by offering the hopeful alternative of political freedom and peaceful change.
p110
aVSo the United States of America supports democratic reform across the broader Middle East.
p111
aVElections are vital, but they are only the beginning.
p112
aVRaising up a democracy requires the rule of law, and protection of minorities, and strong, accountable institutions that last longer than a single vote.
p113
aVThe great people of Egypt have voted in a multi-party presidential election -- and now their government should open paths of peaceful opposition that will reduce the appeal of radicalism.
p114
aVThe Palestinian people have voted in elections.
p115
aVAnd now the leaders of Hamas must recognize Israel, disarm, reject terrorism, and work for lasting peace.
p116
aV(Applause.)
p117
aVSaudi Arabia has taken the first steps of reform -- now it can offer its people a better future by pressing forward with those efforts.
p118
aVDemocracies in the Middle East will not look like our own, because they will reflect the traditions of their own citizens.
p119
aVYet liberty is the future of every nation in the Middle East, because liberty is the right and hope of all humanity.
p120
aV(Applause.)
